Package: fibroquant
Title: Quantify Lung Fibrosis in Histological Images
Version: 0.0.0.9000
Authors@R: 
    person(
        given = "William", 
        family = "Oldham", 
        email = "wm.oldham@gmail.com", 
        role = c("aut", "cre"), 
        comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0003-3029-4866")
    )
Description: Provides tools for quantifying the severity of tissue fibrosis
    from stained histological sections (for example, Masson's trichrome or
    haematoxylin and eosin). A common image-processing front end feeds
    interchangeable scoring methods through a shared interface, so that
    different quantification approaches can be applied and compared. The
    methods are unsupervised and intended for high-throughput analysis of
    large image sets with minimal user input.
